    "Cut the tomatoes into fairly even-sized wedges and\nchunks, either halving small cherry tomatoes or",
    "Heat the grill to medium. Place the cobnuts on a grr\ntray and mix with the rapeseed oil and salt. Grill unt1\nlightly toasted, then leave to cool",
    "leaving them whole.",
    "Chop the pickled walnuts into small pieces and mix\nin a bowl with some of their juice and the rapeseed\noil. Season with salt and pepper to taste.",
    "Toss the salad leaves in the dressing and arrange on\nserving plates or bowls. Break the cheese into pieces\nand scatter over the top of the salad, along with the\ntoasted cobnuts.",
    "Arrange the tomatoes on individual plates or one\nlarge serving platter and spoon over the pickled\nwalnut dressing. Shave the cheese into thin slices\nwith a sharp knife or vegetable peeler and scatter\nover the tomatoes.",
