    "Pour the vegetable stock into a large saucepan, add\nthe leek and celery and bring to a simmer. Season\nlightly with salt and pepper and let simmer for\n15 minutes.",
    "Meanwhile, blanch the broad beans in boiling salted\nwater for 3-4 minutes, then drain and refresh under\nthe cold tap. Remove the tough skins from any larger\nbroad beans; leave small ones as they are.",
    "Cook the beetroot in a pan of salted water for about\n1 hour until they feel tender when pierced with a\nknife. Drain and leave until cool enough to handle,\nthen peel and roughly chop the beetroot.",
    "Heat the oil in a large saucepan, add the onion,\ncover and cook gently for 3- 4 minutes to soften. Add\nthe vegetable stock, bring to the boil, season with\na little salt and pepper and simmer for 30 minutes.",
    "Add the peas and green beans to the simmering\nstock and cook for a further 10 minutes. Add\nthe broad beans, chopped parsley and chives,\nand simmer for another 5 minutes. Re-season if\nnecessary before serving.",
    "I",
    "Add the beetroot, then remove from the heat. Puree\nin a blender until smooth, then pass the soup\nthrough a fine-meshed sieve into a large bowl.\nRe-season if necessary. Cool the soup down, then\nrefrigerate for a few hours until well chilled or put it\ninto the freezer if you're in a rush.",
    "Serve in soup plates topped with a dollop of cream,\ncreme fraTche or soft goat's cheese and a sprinkling\nof grated horseradish.",
    "70",
    "SOUPS",
    "CHILLED GARDEN HERB\nSOUP",
    "Puree the soup in a blender until smooth, then pass\nthrough a medium sieve (rather than a fine one, to\nlet the herb bits through) into a bowl.",
    "Set the bowl over another larger bowl of iced water to\ncool the soup down as quickly as possible (this helps\nto preserve its green colour). Re-season if necessary.",
