    "salt and freshly ground black pepper",
    "Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/gas mark 6. Wrap the\ngarlic bulbs in foil and bake them in the oven for",
    "1 large dill pickle or a few gherkins, finely diced",
    "1 hour. Unwrap and leave until cool enough to\nhandle, then peel away any tough outer skin.",
    "Melt the butter in a heavy-based pan and add the\nonion, garlic and cayenne pepper. Cook gently for\n2- 3 minutes to soften, then stir 1n the flour, followed\nby the tomato puree, cider vinegar, redcurrant 1elly\nand mustard.",
    "Put the garlic into a blender with the parsley,\nmustard, warm duck fat (or chicken pan juices) and\nbreadcrumbs and blend until smooth. Add enough\nmilk to give the sauce a thick pouring consistency\nand season with salt and pepper to taste.",
    "Gradually whisk in the hot beef stock, bring to the\nboil and season lightly with salt and pepper. Simmer\nvery gently for about 15 minutes (a simmer plate or\nheat-diffuser mat is useful here). Add the dill pickle\nand re-season if necessary. The sauce should be\nquite thick, if not continue simmering a little longer.",
