    "Roll out the pastry on a lightly floured surface to\na 5mm thickness. Trim to about 2cm larger all round\nthan the pie dish (or cut discs large enough to cover\nindividual dishes). Brush the edges of the pastry\nwith a little of the beaten egg. Lay the pastry over the\nfilling, pressing the egg-washed sides onto the rim of\nthe dish(es).",
    "salt and freshly ground black pepper",
    "1- 2 tsp cornflour (if needed)",
    "If making a large pie, cut a cross in the centre and\ninsert the reserved lobster head, so it sits proud.\nCut a small slit in the top of individual pies to allow\nsteam to escape. Leave to rest in a cool place for\n30 minutes.",
    "Remove the meat from the lobster tails and claws\nand cut roughly into l cm pieces. Reserve one\nlobster head (if making a large pie). Break the rest\nof the shells up a bit, using a heavy knife. Cut the\nchicken thighs in half, or into thirds if large. Cover\nand refrigerate the lobster and chicken meat.",
