    "Heat a ridged griddle pan or heavy-based frying pan\nand lightly oil it. Cook the puffball for 2- 3 minutes\non each side, then remove and keep warm.",
    "Transfer to the oven and cook for about 1112 hours\nuntil the meat is just coming away from the bone.\nLeave to cool for an hour, then take out the duck\nlegs. Strain the fat into a jar (store in the fridge).",
