    "a couple of handfuls of small tasty salad leaves,\nsuch as pea shoots, buckler leaf sorrel, rocket,",
    "purslane, washed",
    "Tewkesbury mustard dressing (page 55)",
    "Cut the cucumbers in half lengthways and scoop out\nthe seeds with a teaspoon. Cut each half on an angle\ninto l -2cm thick slices.",
    "Cut the offal into lcm chunks and set aside.",
    "Heat a ridged griddle pan or heavy-based frying pan\nover a medium-high heat. Season the lamb chops\nwith salt and pepper, brush with oil and cook for",
    "about 5 minutes on each side, keeping them pink.",
    "Heat a ridged griddle pan or heavy-based frying pan.\nSeason the veal chops with salt and pepper and\nbrush with oil. Cook for about 5 minutes on each\nside, depending on thickness, keeping them nice\nand pink.",
    "Meanwhile, heat the rapeseed 011 in another frying\npan and add the shallots. Fry, stirring, for a minute,\nthen add the cucumber slices. Season with salt\nand pepper and saute over a fairly high heat for",
    "2-3 minutes until tender. Take off the heat and stir\nin the shredded mint.",
    "Meanwhile, heat the rapeseed oil in a heavy-based\nfrying pan. Add the butter and heat until foaming,\nthen season the offal pieces and add them to the\npan. Fry briskly over a high heat for 2-3 minutes\nuntil nicely coloured, but keeping them pink in the\nmiddle. Remove from the pan and put to one side.",
    "Divide the cucumber between warmed plates and\nplace the lamb chops on top to serve",
    "While the offal is cooking, toss the salad leaves with\nthe dressing in a bowl. Add the offal, toss briefly and\narrange on serving plates alongside the chops.",
