    "::.VieLL~sVi - especLaLLtj vv.usseLs.",
    "400ml milk",
    "a good pinch of freshly grated nutmeg",
    "Serves 4",
    "2 garlic cloves, peeled and crushed",
    "salt and freshly ground black pepper",
    "4 large chipping potatoes, such as Yukon Gold,\nSpunta or Mans Piper, peeled",
    "150g Lancashire cheese, grated",
    "vegetable or corn oil for deep-trying",
    "2 tbsp fresh white breadcrumbs",
    "10 garlic cloves, peeled and thinly sliced",
    "1 tbsp chopped parsley",
    "sea salt",
    "Preheat the oven to l 60\u00b0C/gas mark 3. Cut the\nparsnips into rough 2-3cm chunks.",
    "Using a mandolin with a shredding attachment or a\nsharp knife, cut the potatoes into long matchsticks.\nabout 3mm thick. Wash them well in a couple of\nchanges of cold water to remove excess starch, then\ndrain and pat dry on a clean tea towel.",
    "Pour the cream and milk into a saucepan, add the\nnutmeg and garlic, and season generously with salt\nand pepper. Bring to the boil, then turn off the heat\nand leave to cool slightly.",
    "Put the parsnips into a shallow oven proof (gratin-\ntype) dish and mix with all but 1 tbsp of the cheese.\nPour the cream mixture over the top.",
    "Heat an 8cm depth of oil 1n a deep-fat fryer or other\nsuitable deep, heavy pan to 120 l 40\"C. Blanch\nthe matchstick potatoes in manageable batches (a\ncouple of handfuls at a time) for 2-3 minutes, then\nremove with a slotted spoon and drain 1n a colander.",
    "Stand the dish in a roasting tray and pour in enough\nboiling water to come halfway up the side of the dish\n(to create a bain-marie). Cook in the oven for about\nan hour until the parsnips are cooked through.",
    "Increase the temperature of the oil to l 60-180\u00b0C\nand re-fry the potatoes with the garlic slices in\nbatches, moving them around in the pan, until\ngolden and crisp. Remove with a slotted spoon and\ndrain on kitchen paper. Sprinkle with sea salt and\nserve immediately.",
    "Preheat the grill to medium. Mix the breadcrumbs\nwith the chopped parsley and remaining 1 tbsp\ngrated cheese. Scatter over the parsnip bake and\nplace under the grill for a few minutes until golden.\nServe at once, or cover with foil and leave in a low\noven until ready to serve.",
    "Alternatively, you can keep the straw potatoes warm,\nuncovered, on a baking tray in a low oven until ready\nto serve. They should stay crisp but if not you can\nbriefly re-fry them in hot oil to crisp them up again.",
